==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Technicality
<hw>Tech`ni*cal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Technicalities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being technical; technicalness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is technical, or peculiar to any trade,
profession, sect, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>technicalities</qex> of the sect.</q>
<rj><qau>Palfrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Technically</ent>⟦br⟧
